tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: Most parameters are within normal limits. Mildly decreased HbA1c may reflect low average glucose or recent anemia/bleeding. Hematocrit is slightly low, but hemoglobin and erythrocytes are normal, suggesting possible mild dilutional effect or early anemia. Platelet count is normal, but mean platelet volume and distribution width are elevated, which may indicate increased platelet turnover or recent platelet activation. No acute abnormalities detected; recommend clinical correlation and monitoring.
